cs.HCI, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.CYBER, cs.DL 

The paper introduces a tool for online education forums that reduces duplicate posts by monitoring questions as students compose them and continuously suggesting relevant posts. This suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HCI) and natural language processing (cs.CL, cs.IR). Additionally, the tool uses machine learning to recommend relevant posts, which could fall under the categories of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) or deep learning (cs.DL).
